MBOMBELA – Urban House is located where Stoep used to be at Sonpark.  The well-known venue has been completely transformed to the epitome of elegance. There are different sections too – each with a different vibe and function – to satisfy every patron’s mood. Co-owners Claud Kruger and Lasea Swift opened the event by cutting the ribbon.  Beautiful, original paintings by Thandazani Ndlovu adorn the walls and the artist was also in attendance on the night. The opening was certainly spectacular, and guests were treated like royalty. ALSO READ: Mpumalanga High Court officially opened